HEADWORD: Harmine
<hw>Har"mine</hw> <pr>(h⟦aum⟧r"m⟦icr⟧n ⟦or⟧ -m⟦emac⟧n)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos><ety>[See <er>Harmaline</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>An alkaloid accompanying harmaline (in the <spn>Peganum
harmala</spn>), and obtained from it by oxidation. It is a white
crystalline substance.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Harmless</ent>⟦br⟧
